# Tokens

Tokens are the **manufacturing layer** of Pathogen: change a role once in `pathogen.tailwind.css`, and every component that consumes it inherits the update. Implementation code should describe **intent** (`--pvc-color-accent-solid`), not palette stops (`primary-700`).

## Theme Contract

Host applications may override brand colour after importing Pathogen CSS:

| Variable | Default | Host use |
|----------|---------|----------|
| `--color-primary-*` | Tailwind blue scale | Brand / action scale (IRIDA: green) |
| `--color-neutral-*` | Tailwind slate scale | Do not override; use `neutral-*` utilities, not `slate-*` |
| `--font-sans` | Inter-first stack | Optional font swap |
| `--font-mono` | System monospace | Code and identifiers |

**Naming rule:** `neutral-*` is the public API. It aliases slate in theme config. New code must not use raw `slate-*` utilities — they bypass the contract and drift from semantic roles.

## Token Layers

```
Palette (--color-primary-*, --color-neutral-*, status hues)
    ↓
Semantic roles (--pvc-color-*, --type-*, --pvc-radius-*, motion, shadow)
    ↓
Component-scoped (--pvc-data-grid-*, --pvc-tooltip-origin)
```

Component-scoped tokens are internal layout hooks. Do not treat them as host theme overrides.

## Semantic Colour Roles

Swatches show Pathogen default theme values. Host applications map the same roles to different brand values via `--color-primary-*`.

